Issues.Body:
### What problem does this feature solve?
About this issue https://github.com/vuejs/vue-loader/issues/1229, I want to more discuss.

I think you said is right. There will be some logic implement in different component.However, does the parent component need to consider all the details of the child component?

I think when I create a component.I would like to encapsulate all the logic related to this component inside the component.Because the logic should belong to the component.Next time, when use this component in new component, I just need to think about the logic of the new component.

Besides,most applications now require asynchronous requests.Getting status from parent component is very common.So some time I will use ugly way to make it work.

component A
```
<template>
  <div>
    <component-b v-bind:go="ajax"></component-b>
  </div>
</template>
<script>
export default {
  name: "componentA",
  methods: {
    ajax() {
      return httprequest()
    }
  }
}
</script>
```

component B
```
<template>
  <button v-on:click="emit">
    <span v-if="loading">loading...</span>
    <span>component-b</span>
  </button>
</template>
<script>
export default {
  name: "componentB",
  props: ['loading', 'go'],
  methods: {
    emit() {
      this.loading = true
      this.go().then(() => {
        this.loading = false
      })
    }
  }
}
</script>
```

I think it isn't a good way, but it's efficient.

I have found a way to custom event modifiers in `vue-template-compiler`, If you want I can write a demo to show how it's efficient.

🖖

### What does the proposed API look like?
Add an async modifier.


component A 
```
<template>
  <div>
    <component-b v-on:go.async="ajax"></component-b>
  </div>
</template>
<script>
export default {
  name: "componentA",
  methods: {
    ajax() {
      return httprequest()
    }
  }
}
</script>
```
component B
```
<template>
  <button v-on:click="emit">
    <span v-if="loading">loading...</span>
    <span>component-b</span>
  </button>
</template>
<script>
export default {
  name: "componentB",
  props: ['loading'],
  methods: {
    emit() {
      this.loading = true
      this.$emit('go').then(() => {
        this.loading = false
      })
    }
  }
}
</script>
```

